1
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:51,801
FRANKLY SPEAKING

2
00:00:57,682 --> 00:01:00,060
NEWS AT NOON

3
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:04,981
Good afternoon,
and welcome to JBC News at Noon.

4
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:06,232
SONG KI-BAEK

5
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:10,195
It's been four years
since workplace bullying was prohibited

6
00:01:10,278 --> 00:01:14,783
under the revised Labor Standards Act,
which took effect in July 2019.

7
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:18,119
Some say it has contributed
to raising awareness,

8
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:23,333
but many people are still suffering
from workplace conflict and harassment.

9
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:28,046
Kim Seo-jun has more on the story.
Reporter Kim Seo-jun.

10
00:01:30,215 --> 00:01:31,174
Reporter Kim Seo-jun.

11
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:36,346
Reporter Kim Seo-jun?

12
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:39,015
Reporter Kim Seo-jun.

13
00:01:39,974 --> 00:01:41,810
REPORTER KIM SEO-JUN

14
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:46,272
Yes. How are things on Planet Warr?

15
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:50,527
Yes. I'm here because
I received a tip-off that Tyranno Max,

16
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:53,655
the one who protects Planet Warr,

17
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:56,116
forced Agent Harry
to go hunting against his will.

18
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:58,076
He made an herbivore dinosaur go hunting?

19
00:01:58,159 --> 00:02:00,328
That is wrong and unfair.

20
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:04,958
That's right. But Harry has to get
a reference letter from Max,

21
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:07,043
so he's been crying every night.

22
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:09,629
Hey, behave yourself.

23
00:02:09,712 --> 00:02:11,548
Oh, boy. The situation seems serious.

24
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:14,384
Pachycephalosaurus and Brachiosaurus
also belong to

25
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:18,388
the Herbivore Dinosaurs Association.
Has the HDA made any moves yet?

26
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:22,809
I think it's wrong to order others around,
just because you're strong.

27
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:26,729
That wasn't in the script, you know.

28
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:28,106
Dad!

29
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:31,901
-Hold on. Is that a camera?
-Yes, it is.

30
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:32,902
Whoa.

31
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:37,532
Isn't this considered
workplace harassment?

32
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:41,369
Did he really have to bring his son
to work for his work experience?

33
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,165
I really respect Ki-baek.

34
00:02:45,248 --> 00:02:47,667
He came two hours early
and waited on standby for this.

35
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:48,751
-God.
-Look at this.

36
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:50,920
Why would he do this?
He already has it all.

37
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:52,297
He's going overboard.

38
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:56,217
He doesn't have it all.

39
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:59,637
You think it's easy
to get the main news anchor title?

40
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:03,766
It's not like you guys would do this
if he told you to.

41
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:06,269
Mr. Kim pesters you until you give in.

42
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:07,520
Look at that.

43
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:09,522
And Ki-baek knows to put up with it.

44
00:03:09,606 --> 00:03:11,774
I joined JBC
because of Ki-baek's news show.

45
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:13,234
What a letdown.

46
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:15,695
We may be announcers
in front of the camera,

47
00:03:15,778 --> 00:03:17,739
but we're all just employees after all.

48
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:21,409
Don't come any closer!

49
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:25,663
Oh, Ki-baek. The closing line.

50
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:34,213
I sincerely promise you
that I'll only report the truth

51
00:03:34,297 --> 00:03:35,882
and never lie to you.

52
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:40,470
Song Ki-baek, JBC News.

53
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:44,015
All right, let's take a picture.
Everyone, gather around.

54
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:47,769
All right.

55
00:03:47,852 --> 00:03:50,647
One, two, three.

56
00:03:51,856 --> 00:03:52,982
I WANT TO BE A REPORTER!

57
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,151
ANNOUNCER SONG KI-BAEK
WISHING YOU HAPPINESS

58
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,788
All right. Let's get ready!

59
00:04:15,713 --> 00:04:16,839
Be punctual, will you?

60
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:19,801
Just an FYI.
We changed the opening line slightly.

61
00:04:23,388 --> 00:04:26,099
All right. It's 11:57.
We have three minutes.

62
00:04:26,182 --> 00:04:27,100
Stand by.

63
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:31,688
Ki-baek.

64
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:36,109
Be patient, and you'll soon be able
to anchor the main news show.

65
00:04:38,152 --> 00:04:40,363
Kudos for putting up with that
this morning.

66
00:04:41,739 --> 00:04:43,866
Your body reacts to stress right away.

67
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,869
Someone from hair and makeup
bought this from Japan.

68
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:49,330
It's good for the stomach.

69
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,549
Hye-yeon, your phone keeps buzzing.

70
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:10,393
Is something wrong?

71
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:12,312
Yes. What?

72
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:16,858
Hye-yeon, you don't look so well.

73
00:05:16,941 --> 00:05:18,192
Are you all right?

74
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:20,695
Let's focus.

75
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:23,114
-All right, guys. Stand by.
-Stand by.

76
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:24,574
Stand by.

77
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:42,425
Ready.

78
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:44,844
All right. Here we go.

79
00:05:45,595 --> 00:05:46,888
Cue.

80
00:05:51,976 --> 00:05:54,520
EPISODE 1: IT'S A LIE

81
00:05:54,604 --> 00:05:56,105
Good afternoon,

82
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,232
and welcome to JBC News at Noon.

83
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:03,446
Last week saw the highest number
of new flu cases reported since 2000.

84
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:04,530
Enjoy.

85
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:05,573
Thank you.

86
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:10,620
I'm Kim Joo-ho.

87
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:14,248
WRITER HYE-JIN:
DID YOU MEET HIM?

88
00:06:14,332 --> 00:06:15,458
YES, WE MET UP JUST NOW

89
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:16,834
GOOD LUCK

90
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:18,920
Oh, let me.

91
00:06:20,379 --> 00:06:22,131
I'm sitting closer. Just wait here.

92
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:25,301
You're very efficient.

93
00:06:25,384 --> 00:06:28,971
Time is precious, you know.
Let me go get our precious coffee.

94
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:30,348
Sure.

95
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:50,535
Oh, right. On TV, I've seen writers
working away in fancy studios.

96
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:52,411
Not variety show writers.

97
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:54,705
When I'm working,
I don't even have time to sit.

98
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:56,582
I even have to eat standing up.

99
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:58,709
You know the office caste system?

100
00:06:58,793 --> 00:07:01,671
Oh, are writers the second caste?

101
00:07:01,754 --> 00:07:03,047
Then I could sit and work.

102
00:07:03,131 --> 00:07:07,510
If there were ten castes,
then writers would be

103
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:09,262
at rock bottom.

104
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,555
Rock bottom?

105
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:13,141
We have countless annoying, petty tasks.

106
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:17,395
From planning, casting, location scouting,
and from editing to comforting the cast.

107
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:19,522
At times, I wonder
if I'm just an errand girl.

108
00:07:20,398 --> 00:07:23,901
That's right. I am an errand girl.

109
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,945
One who runs all sorts of petty errands.

110
00:07:29,198 --> 00:07:32,201
Well, then you're probably
too busy to date anyone.

111
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:34,620
Oh, please.
We can always find time to date.

112
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:37,457
Years ago, we went to go shoot
in Thailand.

113
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:39,292
Back then, we were so busy.

114
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:42,712
On the day we were coming back,
a writer burst into tears at the airport.

115
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:44,964
I got worried and was like,
"What happened?"

116
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:47,717
All of a sudden,
a handsome Thai boy showed up and…

117
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:59,061
Was Bangkok's full name in the script?
Or is he improvising?

118
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,146
Improvising, I think.

119
00:08:00,229 --> 00:08:02,023
Song Ki-baek never disappoints.

120
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:05,443
A city with a beautiful name, Bangkok.

121
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:11,199
I haven't been to Bangkok,
but to celebrate Visit Thailand Year…

122
00:08:11,282 --> 00:08:14,160
What's with Hye-yeon today?
Did something happen?

123
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:15,286
I wonder too.

124
00:08:15,369 --> 00:08:18,080
Most people don't know
Bangkok's full name.

125
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:21,417
You must be very interested in Thailand.

126
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:22,835
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

127
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:25,338
Ki-baek is on a roll these days.

128
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:27,089
This show's ratings have gone up.

129
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:29,675
Also, I heard he was born
into a wealthy family.

130
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:32,470
He's from a good family
on top of being competent and kind.

131
00:08:33,054 --> 00:08:36,015
He has it all, which is clearly why
he's always so relaxed.

132
00:08:36,098 --> 00:08:36,974
I'm jealous.

133
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:39,060
That's why we call him
the blue-chip stock.

134
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:43,648
The main anchor position always goes to
the young and rich, the tall and handsome.

135
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:46,067
He'll be the main anchor
of the nine o'clock news.

136
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:48,194
He'd be the first male announcer to do it.

137
00:08:48,277 --> 00:08:49,570
-Really?
-Yes.

138
00:08:49,654 --> 00:08:52,156
Must be nice to be that successful
at a young age.

139
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:55,076
Way to go.

140
00:08:55,159 --> 00:08:56,577
So what's happening now?

141
00:08:57,161 --> 00:08:58,913
Just keep him there a few more minutes.

142
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:01,165
I'll be right there. Okay, I have to go.

143
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:04,961
Was that one of those "annoying" tasks?

144
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:07,004
That's right.

145
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:10,466
If someone you know
wants to be a variety show writer,

146
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,717
talk them out of it.

147
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:14,845
Variety shows are really fun
when you're watching them.

148
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:17,765
I'm a huge fan of Men on the Run.

149
00:09:17,848 --> 00:09:20,476
I rush home from work
to watch it and enjoy a solo drink.

150
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,687
-You're a Men on the Run fan?
-Sorry?

151
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:24,564
It's why I can put up with my job.

152
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:27,733
Falling asleep, laughing after eating
in the comfort of your own home.

153
00:09:27,817 --> 00:09:29,318
It feels so awesome.

154
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:32,780
That's why I can't run away
from this hellhole.

155
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:36,409
-Oh, boy.
-Right.

156
00:09:36,492 --> 00:09:37,326
Yes.

157
00:09:41,038 --> 00:09:41,872
I see.

158
00:09:45,293 --> 00:09:48,212
Email me the details, and I'll go over it.

159
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:51,882
As you already know,
the show is quite popular.

160
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:53,801
Appearing in it is great marketing.

161
00:09:53,884 --> 00:09:56,971
The doctor on the previous team
opened a new clinic in Gangnam.

162
00:09:57,471 --> 00:09:58,306
I see.

163
00:09:59,348 --> 00:10:01,684
Oh, you can get going. You seem busy.

164
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:05,813
Variety show writers have
such a tough job.

165
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:08,649
Being unfunny is what's stressful for us,
not being busy.

166
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:13,029
Anyway, I really have to go.
I'll be in touch.

167
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:15,573
All right. Bye.

168
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:18,117
Yes, I'll be there shortly.

169
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,785
I told you I'd be right there.

170
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:23,581
About 20 minutes?
Hold on. No. Ten minutes.

171
00:10:23,664 --> 00:10:25,875
I bet she really has no time to date.

172
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:29,378
ON WOO-JU
MEN ON THE RUN WRITER

173
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:30,463
It's such a shame.

174
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:33,507
The system must be expanded

175
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:36,260
so children in need
will no longer be left out.

176
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:40,473
Hye-yeon, your phone keeps buzzing.

177
00:10:41,932 --> 00:10:44,393
HUSBAND: I'LL TEACH YOU TWO
A LESSON, JUST WAIT AND SEE

178
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:59,033
Hye-yeon, aren't you
going to say your line?

179
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:04,163
As adults, it is our duty
to protect children.

180
00:11:04,246 --> 00:11:06,749
It's important to pay attention
in your day-to-day life.

181
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:10,378
VCR, cue.

182
00:11:13,464 --> 00:11:14,507
-Hey!
-Yes.

183
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:15,549
Are you insane?

184
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:17,885
The director is watching this.

185
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:19,970
Another reshuffle is coming.
Get it together!

186
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:22,515
Hye-yeon.

187
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:24,100
Let's focus, okay?

188
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,269
Camera three, show Ki-baek.

189
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,774
Here's today's weather.

190
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:47,331
-Hello.
-Where is he?

191
00:11:47,415 --> 00:11:49,959
Oh, the producer told us
not to call you, but--

192
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:51,669
Then you shouldn't have called me.

193
00:11:51,752 --> 00:11:53,546
He said no female guests.

194
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:56,966
Why? Yesterday, he even said he'd go
to the salon early to prep for the shoot.

195
00:11:57,049 --> 00:11:58,217
Well, the thing is…

196
00:11:58,300 --> 00:11:59,218
What's the problem?

197
00:11:59,301 --> 00:12:00,136
Well…

198
00:12:01,595 --> 00:12:03,431
-His girlfriend won't let him.
-Quiet.

199
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:04,348
What?

200
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:06,559
He can't even make eye contact
with other women.

201
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:09,895
No, that's…

202
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:12,940
It's fish sauce. She drank it.

203
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:16,861
It's weak. Put in more fish sauce.

204
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:18,237
This won't do.

205
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,947
-What?
-Isn't this fish sauce?

206
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,198
Yes, it's strong enough.

207
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:22,658
Jesus.

208
00:12:23,242 --> 00:12:27,163
Listen, trust me on this.
I'll make you look like Chae Chi-su today.

209
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:31,500
The team captain who only thinks about
basketball and his team. What do you say?

210
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:34,420
I can't be in the same frame
with the female guests.

211
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:37,965
Can't you just say
I'm not feeling well today?

212
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:42,344
I mean, I could.
But the show's called Men on the Run.

213
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:43,804
You need to actually run.

214
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:45,931
I'll tweak things
so you'll have no issues.

215
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:49,894
Who is she?

216
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:54,940
Who is it this time? Tell me.
I'll go and persuade her.

217
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:55,858
What? Cut it out.

218
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:59,278
Because of her,
you can't think rationally right now.

219
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:00,196
Punch in her number.

220
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:03,073
It's because
I'm really not feeling well today.

221
00:13:03,157 --> 00:13:06,285
Hey, Kim Seong-hun! Who is she?

222
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:14,084
Isn't that your husband?

223
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:19,089
-What are you doing? Get out!
-Honey?

224
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:20,132
Director!

225
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:21,800
Kim Seong-hun, you son of a bitch!

226
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:26,055
Kim Seong-hun should be punished
for destroying my family.

227
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:28,349
He slept with my wife. That…

228
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:38,150
Wait, I-- Hold on.

229
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:42,696
You all need to know the truth
about that bastard who slept with my wife!

230
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:44,532
Please don't do this. We're on air.

231
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:45,491
-Why not?
-Get out!

232
00:13:45,574 --> 00:13:47,660
I'm doing this to get you guys in trouble.

233
00:13:52,706 --> 00:13:54,833
I apologize.

234
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:56,835
That was an unexpected--

235
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:05,177
I apologize for the interruption.
Please understand--

236
00:14:05,261 --> 00:14:08,722
Kim Seong-hun, you scumbag.
Do you know who I am? You bastard.

237
00:14:08,806 --> 00:14:10,975
You'd better come here now. Right now!

238
00:14:12,101 --> 00:14:13,060
Please…

239
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:19,483
What are you waiting for?
Switch on the ending signal!

240
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:21,610
Call the police. Dial 112.

241
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:23,988
Hey! What is going on?

242
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,449
What is happening?

243
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:28,367
Let go.

244
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:30,661
What are you waiting for? Switch that off.

245
00:14:30,744 --> 00:14:32,079
Hurry!

246
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:42,214
The ending signal!

247
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:45,009
Someone barged into the studio.

248
00:14:47,386 --> 00:14:48,345
At noon…

249
00:14:49,179 --> 00:14:52,141
WHO WATCHES THE NEWS THESE DAYS?

250
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:55,311
ISN'T IT ALL FAKE NEWS ANYWAY?

251
00:14:57,354 --> 00:14:58,647
I sincerely promise you

252
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:01,483
that I'll only report the truth
and never lie to you.

253
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,443
NEWS AT NOON

254
00:15:02,526 --> 00:15:03,944
A NEW BEGINNING FOR KOREAN NEWS

255
00:15:05,154 --> 00:15:06,196
Security!

256
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:09,116
Security!

257
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:13,078
You're just going to leave?

258
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:14,246
-Woo-ju!
-Woo-ju!

259
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:15,456
What now?

260
00:15:15,539 --> 00:15:18,667
We have a big problem.
Seong-hun's name is all over the news.

261
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:20,210
-What do you mean?
-Woo-ju, look.

262
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:22,963
KIM SEONG-HUN HAVING AN AFFAIR?

263
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:27,384
-I'm screwed. Hey, let's go!
-But…

264
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:29,595
What? Wait, Seong-hun!

265
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,264
Oh, no.

266
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:37,853
My gosh. They're 12 years apart.

267
00:15:37,937 --> 00:15:39,146
Seriously.

268
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:47,738
My apologies. It's all my fault.
I should've handled it better.

269
00:15:47,821 --> 00:15:50,240
Of course. Clearly, it's not my fault.

270
00:15:50,324 --> 00:15:52,868
How was I supposed to know in advance

271
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,704
that the announcer's husband
would cause a scene

272
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:58,248
because his wife was having an affair
with Seong-hun?

273
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:07,549
I'm sorry. I understand I should
take responsibility as the head writer.

274
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:08,634
Why are you sorry?

275
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:12,262
Those cheaters owe us an apology.
Why are you always apologizing?

276
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:13,806
KIM SANG-JIN

277
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:16,016
Damn it.

278
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:20,562
How dare they bring an abominable
personal matter into the news studio?

279
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:24,692
This happens when people don't separate
their personal and professional lives.

280
00:16:25,609 --> 00:16:26,610
You know?

281
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:29,154
-Right?
-Yes.

282
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:30,781
You're absolutely right.

283
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:33,659
But we do have to follow the protocol,

284
00:16:33,742 --> 00:16:35,995
so we'll need to submit a report.

285
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:40,874
It's really embarrassing though, you know?

286
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:43,627
So you take care of it
and get it sorted out.

287
00:16:43,711 --> 00:16:44,586
Sure.

288
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:46,255
Ensure uninvolved parties aren't affected.

289
00:16:46,338 --> 00:16:48,590
Especially people like…

290
00:16:49,508 --> 00:16:50,634
Like me.

291
00:16:51,885 --> 00:16:52,720
Yes, sir.

292
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:54,888
You can go now.

293
00:16:57,641 --> 00:17:00,310
Oh, about the audition
for the main anchor position.

294
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:04,064
Yes. You said you'd give me
an update today.

295
00:17:04,148 --> 00:17:07,401
I got your name on the list of candidates.

296
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:08,318
I see.

297
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:10,362
But the thing is,

298
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:14,742
I'm not sure if it's a good thing
or a bad thing.

299
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:16,493
What do you mean?

300
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:21,373
You know, your face is everywhere
because of the incident on the news today.

301
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:25,085
Everyone in the country
knows your name now.

302
00:17:25,794 --> 00:17:30,799
You see, I think it could help you out,
but at the same time…

303
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:38,348
So it could give me a competitive edge
over the other candidates?

304
00:17:39,808 --> 00:17:41,060
That's right.

305
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:45,355
So don't be discouraged.
Go and get ready for the audition.

306
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:49,068
I'll prepare thoroughly and do my best
so I won't miss this opportunity.

307
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:52,321
Oh, Seong-gyu! Mr. Superstar.

308
00:17:52,404 --> 00:17:54,281
To what do I owe the pleasure?

309
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:57,076
What? You can go.

310
00:17:58,327 --> 00:17:59,745
Hey, well…

311
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:02,372
Can I get your autograph? Just a couple.

312
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,169
CHEATING AND PUNISHMENT
BIZARRE TV NEWS BLUNDER

313
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,176
Guess your shoot ended early.

314
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:16,220
Yes.

315
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:21,475
Tantan had to attend an event
in the countryside, so we ended early.

316
00:18:22,434 --> 00:18:25,729
Hey, are you all right? I read the story.

317
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:29,149
Your face looked awful in that photo.

318
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:34,822
Who cares about my face?
It destroyed the news program's dignity.

319
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:36,240
Spoken like a true anchorman.

320
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:41,161
Oh, right. I heard you
turned down Golden Family.

321
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:42,871
For the episode featuring announcers.

322
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:45,541
Everyone wants to be on that show.

323
00:18:45,624 --> 00:18:48,627
Do you even visit your family these days?

324
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:51,713
Your mom's been calling me.
She said she couldn't reach you.

325
00:18:53,882 --> 00:18:55,175
God, you scared me.

326
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:56,343
Oh, I'm sorry.

327
00:18:56,426 --> 00:18:57,803
I see that you're working hard.

328
00:18:59,596 --> 00:19:01,849
Man, you handled that so well.

329
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:03,934
I would've peed my pants, for sure.

330
00:19:04,434 --> 00:19:06,645
Are you really going to
turn down Golden Family?

331
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:10,065
They said they'd contact me
if you said no.

332
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:13,569
Oh, it doesn't work with my schedule.
You should do it.

333
00:19:16,655 --> 00:19:18,991
Heard your family can't do it.
Do they live far away?

334
00:19:19,074 --> 00:19:20,242
Yes.

335
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:21,368
Do they live abroad?

336
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:23,579
Oh… Hey, I'm off.

337
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:25,664
Well, they live far away.

338
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:29,668
So you live alone in that big house
in Seongsu-dong?

339
00:19:30,335 --> 00:19:33,172
Rumor has it you'd make headlines
in the finance section

340
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:36,675
if your house were to be revealed.
Is it true?

341
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:39,261
It must be true.

342
00:19:39,344 --> 00:19:43,056
No wonder Mr. Kim always has your back
and no one else's.

343
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,766
What do you mean, he has my back?

344
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,476
All he does is dump work on me.

345
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,936
You know how he is.

346
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:52,232
He's keeping you by his side
because he knows he can benefit from it.

347
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:05,037
Will I really be all right?

348
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:07,915
Mr. Kim, please put in a good word for me.

349
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:11,793
It's the stress.

350
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:15,714
Cancel the show?
Are you really going to do this to me?

351
00:20:15,797 --> 00:20:18,550
When you asked me to help
a program pulling in 3% in ratings,

352
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:21,178
I pulled all-nighters for three months
without complaining.

353
00:20:21,261 --> 00:20:24,181
Now, the ratings are at a whopping 18%.

354
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:28,644
All right, I heard you.
Then persuade the no-show first.

355
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:32,439
Sure thing.
You cannot cancel the show, ma'am.

356
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:35,275
Woo-ju, you'd better step up your game.

357
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:38,987
I heard your rival show on tvM
might cast Kim Jeong-heon.

358
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:40,739
-Who?
-My goodness.

359
00:20:40,822 --> 00:20:43,742
You don't know who Kim Jeong-heon is?
Everyone's ideal son-in-law.

360
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:45,619
Mr. Honey Bunny.

361
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:47,955
The doors are closing.

362
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:04,429
Hello? Hey.

363
00:21:12,145 --> 00:21:14,231
CLOSED FOR INSPECTION

364
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:16,525
When people get off, you can get started.

365
00:21:17,150 --> 00:21:18,026
…get started.

366
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:21,530
Has he lost his mind?
How dare he say he'll drop out?

367
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:24,408
Hey, make sure Mr. Kim doesn't leave.

368
00:21:24,491 --> 00:21:26,785
I'll be there in three… No, in one minute.

369
00:21:26,868 --> 00:21:29,538
Make sure he doesn't leave
until I get there.

370
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:31,039
Do whatever it takes.

371
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:35,377
Well, lock the door or cause a scene.
I'll be there shortly, okay?

372
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:38,755
What? I can't hear you.
I'm in the elevator now.

373
00:21:40,382 --> 00:21:42,134
I said, I'm in the elevator now.

374
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:47,472
What?

375
00:21:49,057 --> 00:21:49,891
What is this?

376
00:21:58,775 --> 00:22:00,485
Nothing's going my way today.

377
00:22:07,617 --> 00:22:10,746
Mr. Song Ki-baek?
Can you give me a hand?

378
00:22:13,457 --> 00:22:16,710
It's dangerous to force open the doors
when the elevator's not working.

379
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:20,464
I know that because I worked on
Emergency Escape Number 3,

380
00:22:20,547 --> 00:22:22,341
but I don't have time for this.

381
00:22:22,424 --> 00:22:24,593
Maybe they're doing a routine inspection,

382
00:22:24,676 --> 00:22:26,094
so let's wait a bit.

383
00:22:36,396 --> 00:22:37,814
Did you fart?

384
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:40,275
Did you poop?

385
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:42,944
No, I did not.

386
00:22:44,154 --> 00:22:48,575
Also, the official medical term
is "flatulence," not "fart."

387
00:22:49,701 --> 00:22:51,369
Okay. So it was a wet fart.

388
00:22:53,163 --> 00:22:54,623
Ouch.

389
00:22:58,126 --> 00:22:59,920
Hurry up and help me open this!

390
00:23:00,003 --> 00:23:02,297
It was just a fart this time,
but if it happens again,

391
00:23:02,380 --> 00:23:03,840
you won't be able to hold it in.

392
00:23:03,924 --> 00:23:07,135
I can't really move
or use my physical strength right now.

393
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:08,804
Seriously.

394
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:11,264
I guess I've been under a lot of stress.

395
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:13,517
And I think I have indigestion.

396
00:23:14,101 --> 00:23:15,310
Don't care, didn't ask.

397
00:23:15,393 --> 00:23:16,978
Just don't poop in here.

398
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:18,772
Don't you worry.

399
00:23:25,946 --> 00:23:27,989
They're under inspection.
Use that elevator.

400
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:32,160
-It's over there.
-Hello?

401
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:34,996
Hello? We're trapped in here!

402
00:23:35,789 --> 00:23:38,166
We're in this elevator.

403
00:23:40,377 --> 00:23:44,172
What do we do?
Hello? We're trapped in here!

404
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:45,966
We're inside!

405
00:23:46,049 --> 00:23:47,175
You're in the elevator?

406
00:23:47,259 --> 00:23:49,427
Yes, we're trapped in here!

407
00:23:49,511 --> 00:23:50,428
One moment!

408
00:23:56,351 --> 00:23:57,978
-Are you okay?
-Yes, I'm all right.

409
00:23:58,061 --> 00:23:59,855
Okay, just one moment.

410
00:23:59,938 --> 00:24:00,814
Okay.

411
00:24:02,732 --> 00:24:04,192
Can you move?

412
00:24:07,404 --> 00:24:10,824
Well, I'm in a rush too. Cheer up.

413
00:24:11,992 --> 00:24:12,993
Pull me out, please.

414
00:24:16,997 --> 00:24:18,498
-Are you all right?
-Thank you.

415
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:20,500
Yes, I'm coming.

416
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:21,668
Are you all right?

417
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:24,171
What are you doing?
You don't want to come out?

418
00:24:27,132 --> 00:24:28,008
Hurry up.

419
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:32,262
Come on out!

420
00:24:33,221 --> 00:24:34,556
Keep out!

421
00:24:38,143 --> 00:24:39,144
Is he okay?

422
00:24:39,227 --> 00:24:40,478
What should we do?

423
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:41,605
Are you okay?

424
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:43,023
Did something bad happen?

425
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:08,215
Man, it's only 3:00 p.m.

426
00:25:14,054 --> 00:25:15,222
JBC, WE CAN DO IT!

427
00:25:15,305 --> 00:25:17,682
SMOKE-FREE FOR 87 DAYS,
ANNOUNCER SONG KI-BAEK

428
00:25:25,523 --> 00:25:27,442
How about a beer after work?

429
00:25:27,525 --> 00:25:30,153
-I'm supposed to see my friends today.
-Damn.

430
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:32,864
Oh, right. The audition for main anchor.

431
00:25:32,948 --> 00:25:35,158
I heard some announcers were applying too.

432
00:25:35,242 --> 00:25:37,160
I heard Song Ki-baek was doing it.

433
00:25:37,244 --> 00:25:39,371
Hey, buddy. We have to bring our A-game.

434
00:25:39,454 --> 00:25:43,458
The main anchor is like the face of JBC.
We can't let an announcer take the job.

435
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:47,087
Why not? Because it has never happened
in the history of JBC.

436
00:25:47,170 --> 00:25:48,463
Come here.

437
00:25:48,546 --> 00:25:52,425
When the CEO is finalizing his decision,
he collects the employees' opinions.

438
00:25:52,509 --> 00:25:57,472
He asks all the producers and directors
what they think about the candidates.

439
00:25:57,555 --> 00:25:59,224
Oh, I see.

440
00:26:02,185 --> 00:26:03,061
Hello, Mr. Song.

441
00:26:05,063 --> 00:26:06,022
Ki-baek!

442
00:26:06,106 --> 00:26:07,607
Director Kim, why…

443
00:26:07,691 --> 00:26:09,067
Hey, are you free now?

444
00:26:09,150 --> 00:26:10,735
I have a no-show for a live show.

445
00:26:10,819 --> 00:26:12,779
Can you spare me an hour…
No, half an hour.

446
00:26:12,862 --> 00:26:15,907
Oh, I'm sorry.
I really want to help you, but…

447
00:26:15,991 --> 00:26:19,286
When the CEO is finalizing his decision,
he collects the employees' opinions.

448
00:26:19,369 --> 00:26:23,456
He asks all the producers and directors
what they think about the candidates.

449
00:26:23,540 --> 00:26:26,084
I mean, I want to help you, so I will.
Let's go.

450
00:26:26,918 --> 00:26:29,170
This way.

451
00:26:30,922 --> 00:26:32,257
THROW OUT

452
00:26:40,181 --> 00:26:42,767
Guys, we have to do the shoot this week.

453
00:26:42,851 --> 00:26:44,853
If not, we'll all be screwed.

454
00:26:44,936 --> 00:26:46,563
-Let's make it happen.
-Yes, ma'am.

455
00:26:46,646 --> 00:26:48,732
I-na, that profile I printed earlier…

456
00:26:55,322 --> 00:26:57,907
It's removable, right?

457
00:26:57,991 --> 00:26:59,659
Last time, you used waterproof…

458
00:27:00,910 --> 00:27:03,913
I threw out
those waterproof face markers right away.

459
00:27:03,997 --> 00:27:06,374
This is a PPL product,
so I want to test it--

460
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:07,292
Okay.

461
00:27:08,126 --> 00:27:09,919
I just want to test it.

462
00:27:10,587 --> 00:27:12,088
Keep your eyes peeled.

463
00:27:12,172 --> 00:27:13,715
The pay…

464
00:27:14,549 --> 00:27:18,094
Announcers are our only option if we
consider the pay and the tight schedule.

465
00:27:19,596 --> 00:27:21,598
Do we really have to play
this game right now?

466
00:27:21,681 --> 00:27:25,810
Woo-ju said we should try things ourselves
to make sure they'll be successful.

467
00:27:25,894 --> 00:27:27,854
Yes, it could help us come up
with useful ideas…

468
00:27:29,272 --> 00:27:30,315
Here. Go for it.

469
00:27:33,193 --> 00:27:35,362
-I'm sorry.
-Do we really have no one else?

470
00:27:35,445 --> 00:27:37,155
EMPLOYEE RECORD, SONG KI-BAEK

471
00:27:38,365 --> 00:27:40,367
Damn it. What's "announcer" in Korean?

472
00:27:40,450 --> 00:27:41,743
Ki-baek! This way.

473
00:27:41,826 --> 00:27:43,787
-Quick!
-Go inside and get ready!

474
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:45,121
We're good now. He's here.

475
00:27:45,205 --> 00:27:47,749
Get ready! Ki-baek, go inside. Get ready.

476
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:48,792
We can do this.

477
00:27:49,376 --> 00:27:52,003
Just change the opening line.
I trust you'll do great!

478
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:56,549
Calm down. Okay, ready.

479
00:28:01,846 --> 00:28:02,847
Now, we're on.

480
00:28:05,683 --> 00:28:11,147
Hello. I'm Song Ki-baek, the special DJ
for The Man Who Reads Poetry.

481
00:28:14,067 --> 00:28:16,694
I-na. Hey, I-na.

482
00:28:20,156 --> 00:28:21,157
I-na.

483
00:28:22,450 --> 00:28:23,326
I-na!

484
00:28:27,455 --> 00:28:28,957
How many days have you not changed?

485
00:28:31,209 --> 00:28:32,293
Nine days.

486
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:38,133
Don't go to the sauna.
Use this to cab home.

487
00:28:39,259 --> 00:28:40,427
Go home and come back.

488
00:28:41,136 --> 00:28:42,262
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

489
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:45,348
No, not for you.

490
00:28:49,310 --> 00:28:50,812
-Ouch.
-What's so interesting?

491
00:28:50,895 --> 00:28:52,564
I want in on it.

492
00:28:52,647 --> 00:28:54,816
This is the real-time chat
for a radio show.

493
00:28:54,899 --> 00:28:56,401
A radio show? Is it funny?

494
00:28:56,484 --> 00:28:59,070
A close friend of mine is one
of the show's writers.

495
00:28:59,154 --> 00:29:01,156
They have a special DJ for the day,

496
00:29:01,239 --> 00:29:03,199
and the regular listeners are teasing him.

497
00:29:03,283 --> 00:29:04,409
Want to take a listen?

498
00:29:04,492 --> 00:29:08,288
You're monitoring someone else's show?
Way to go, I-na. Let's hear it.

499
00:29:10,999 --> 00:29:14,836
In this segment,
the poems you requested are read.

500
00:29:14,919 --> 00:29:16,755
The next poem is…

501
00:29:16,838 --> 00:29:19,215
I'M SORRY

502
00:29:35,064 --> 00:29:37,066
"Upo Wetland" by Kim Ba-da.

503
00:29:38,359 --> 00:29:41,905
"The Upo Wetland shrouded by fog
