00:43:47,583 --> 00:43:52,546
Sure, but aren't those press conferences
normally held in the early afternoon?

749
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:54,423
The director invited me
to their team dinner.

750
00:43:55,257 --> 00:43:56,383
Cover my shift, please.

751
00:44:02,514 --> 00:44:04,350
Right, I only have 30 minutes.

752
00:44:08,937 --> 00:44:11,065
Why didn't you erase it?
I can see it clearly.

753
00:44:11,148 --> 00:44:12,941
Well, Sol likes this.

754
00:44:13,025 --> 00:44:15,069
What are you going to do
about the variety show?

755
00:44:15,152 --> 00:44:17,613
Did you say you had a bad ankle?
Do they not care?

756
00:44:17,696 --> 00:44:22,034
Thought they'd give up if I made excuses,
but they even called Mr. Kim.

757
00:44:22,117 --> 00:44:23,869
They even know I went hiking last week.

758
00:44:23,952 --> 00:44:25,788
Then try and persuade Mr. Kim.

759
00:44:25,871 --> 00:44:28,499
No, just go ahead and rebel.

760
00:44:28,582 --> 00:44:30,626
Have it out with him.
Tell him you want a news show.

761
00:44:30,709 --> 00:44:33,045
Hey, that's crazy talk.

762
00:44:33,128 --> 00:44:35,172
If you don't think you can persuade him,

763
00:44:35,255 --> 00:44:38,050
then just accept it.

764
00:44:38,133 --> 00:44:39,760
Everyone is supportive of the idea.

765
00:44:39,843 --> 00:44:41,970
Gaining variety show experience
wouldn't be bad.

766
00:44:42,054 --> 00:44:44,723
Being supportive?
They're trying to push me out.

767
00:44:44,807 --> 00:44:48,477
You took on Pyororong Witch School
thinking it'd be a one-off appearance,

768
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:50,813
but it's been five years.

769
00:44:50,896 --> 00:44:52,856
I'm doing this because Sol likes it.

770
00:44:54,483 --> 00:44:56,443
You know how hard I worked to become

771
00:44:56,527 --> 00:44:59,196
the first male announcer
to get the main anchor title.

772
00:44:59,279 --> 00:45:01,407
My efforts are about to go down the drain.

773
00:45:01,490 --> 00:45:05,327
Then keep acting up and tell them
you'd rather die than do it.

774
00:45:05,411 --> 00:45:07,413
What will happen to my image, then?

775
00:45:07,496 --> 00:45:08,664
For God's sake.

776
00:45:10,374 --> 00:45:11,375
You figure it out.

777
00:45:26,723 --> 00:45:29,726
MR. KIM: I TOLD THEM
YOU DECIDED TO DO MEN ON THE RUN

778
00:45:39,528 --> 00:45:41,280
IT'S ON WOO-JU, THE WRITER

779
00:45:41,363 --> 00:45:43,365
PLEASE SAVE MY NUMBER

780
00:46:02,676 --> 00:46:05,471
NATIONAL DODGEBALL CHAMPIONSHIP
A STEP TO VICTORY

781
00:46:22,404 --> 00:46:23,363
MEN ON THE RUN

782
00:46:23,447 --> 00:46:25,073
LET'S PLAY TOGETHER
AND HAVE FUN!

783
00:46:25,157 --> 00:46:26,825
PN!

784
00:46:26,909 --> 00:46:29,286
PN, look here and strike a pose.

785
00:46:31,330 --> 00:46:32,623
Oh, hey. Careful.

786
00:46:32,706 --> 00:46:34,833
-You have something on your face.
-I do? What?

787
00:46:34,917 --> 00:46:36,335
Handsomeness!

788
00:46:36,418 --> 00:46:38,462
Thank you. You have something here.

789
00:46:39,546 --> 00:46:41,048
Would you take a picture with me?

790
00:46:41,131 --> 00:46:42,257
No photos, please.

791
00:46:42,841 --> 00:46:44,092
It's all right.

792
00:46:44,176 --> 00:46:45,719
All right, I love you all.

793
00:46:45,802 --> 00:46:47,679
Don't wait for me out in the cold.

794
00:46:47,763 --> 00:46:49,348
No, we will wait for you!

795
00:46:49,431 --> 00:46:51,808
-We love you, PN!
-We love you, PN!

796
00:46:51,892 --> 00:46:53,393
Ditto!

797
00:46:55,395 --> 00:46:56,355
I love you!

798
00:46:57,481 --> 00:46:58,607
LET'S PLAY TOGETHER!

799
00:46:58,690 --> 00:46:59,691
SOLOMON'S SEAL TEA

800
00:46:59,775 --> 00:47:00,817
LET'S PLAY TOGETHER!

801
00:47:00,901 --> 00:47:02,319
MEN ON THE RUN, LET'S HAVE FUN!

802
00:47:02,402 --> 00:47:04,655
Oh, hello.

803
00:47:04,738 --> 00:47:06,323
Yes, hello.

804
00:47:06,406 --> 00:47:08,492
-Hello.
-Hello.

805
00:47:08,575 --> 00:47:10,244
-Hello.
-Hello!

806
00:47:10,786 --> 00:47:11,787
Wait.

807
00:47:12,829 --> 00:47:14,790
Oh, we're wearing the same shoes.

808
00:47:16,959 --> 00:47:18,794
Great minds think alike.

809
00:47:18,877 --> 00:47:20,462
-We'll catch up in a bit.
-See you.

810
00:47:20,546 --> 00:47:21,672
A MEN'S BALL GAME
AND THEIR SHOWDOWN!

811
00:47:21,755 --> 00:47:22,756
MEN ON THE RUN

812
00:47:38,355 --> 00:47:39,815
You said it was a limited edition.

813
00:47:39,898 --> 00:47:41,650
You said there were
only three pairs nationwide.

814
00:47:41,733 --> 00:47:43,277
Yeah, I know.

815
00:47:43,360 --> 00:47:46,238
Who knew we'd see two of them here?

816
00:47:46,321 --> 00:47:48,240
Do you want to wear something else?

817
00:47:51,034 --> 00:47:52,119
Why should I do that?

818
00:47:52,202 --> 00:47:54,663
Go tell that idiot
to wear different shoes.

819
00:47:58,375 --> 00:47:59,334
I'm barefoot.

820
00:47:59,418 --> 00:48:02,170
I'll have a talk
with his stylist, all right?

821
00:48:02,254 --> 00:48:03,922
Don't blame it on me. Be diplomatic.

822
00:48:04,506 --> 00:48:06,883
He promised to sing on my new single,

823
00:48:06,967 --> 00:48:08,385
so don't make me look like a jerk.

824
00:48:08,468 --> 00:48:11,513
-All right.
-Oh, PN. Here's your milk.

825
00:48:17,603 --> 00:48:19,605
-What the hell?
-What's wrong?

826
00:48:20,814 --> 00:48:22,107
I wanted soy milk!

827
00:48:22,190 --> 00:48:23,025
Soy milk?

828
00:48:23,108 --> 00:48:25,527
I get diarrhea when I drink milk
on an empty stomach.

829
00:48:26,194 --> 00:48:27,112
I drink lactose-free.

830
00:48:27,195 --> 00:48:29,448
Oh, I thought I heard you say
you wanted milk.

831
00:48:29,531 --> 00:48:30,824
I never said that, you little--

832
00:48:30,907 --> 00:48:31,908
Hello, PN!

833
00:48:33,201 --> 00:48:35,037
-You're here.
-Hello.

834
00:48:35,120 --> 00:48:36,705
Did you practice playing dodgeball?

835
00:48:37,331 --> 00:48:38,874
Oh, I took the ball.

836
00:48:38,957 --> 00:48:41,710
I took it with me when I went
to record the music show.

837
00:48:41,793 --> 00:48:43,170
Oh, my.

838
00:48:43,253 --> 00:48:45,881
Anyway, are you the only cast member
in this room?

839
00:48:46,798 --> 00:48:48,759
Where did he go?

840
00:49:02,189 --> 00:49:03,565
What are you doing there?

841
00:49:06,026 --> 00:49:08,654
Oh, I had a nap on the couch in the back.

842
00:49:08,737 --> 00:49:12,074
I conked out.

843
00:49:14,451 --> 00:49:15,494
You should meet everyone.

844
00:49:15,577 --> 00:49:16,745
Come out and say hi.

845
00:49:17,621 --> 00:49:18,455
Say hi.

846
00:49:18,538 --> 00:49:21,792
I bet you've never worked with
a K-pop idol on a show before. Right?

847
00:49:23,251 --> 00:49:25,253
Hello. I'm PN.

848
00:49:26,171 --> 00:49:27,631
I can call you "bro," right?

849
00:49:27,714 --> 00:49:29,424
Oh. Yes, PN.

850
00:49:32,469 --> 00:49:35,764
Please talk casually
once the shoot begins.

851
00:49:40,227 --> 00:49:42,396
All right, Men on the Run.
And we're rolling!

852
00:49:43,355 --> 00:49:46,108
Hello, viewers of Men on the Run.
It's nice to meet you.

853
00:49:46,191 --> 00:49:47,609
Today's game is a big match.

854
00:49:47,693 --> 00:49:49,403
-Yes.
-I'm really excited for it.

855
00:49:49,486 --> 00:49:53,240
Men on the Run versus
Donkeys the Dodgeball Kings.

856
00:49:53,323 --> 00:49:55,200
-It begins now.
-Yes, so it begins.

857
00:49:55,283 --> 00:49:57,285
Ki-baek and PN are getting ready
for the jump ball.

858
00:49:57,369 --> 00:49:58,203
Yes.

859
00:49:59,538 --> 00:50:00,831
It's in their court now.

860
00:50:00,914 --> 00:50:03,333
Song Ki-baek got the ball.
Then it went to Kim Chan-u.

861
00:50:03,417 --> 00:50:04,668
Pass it over.

862
00:50:04,751 --> 00:50:07,754
It's passed back to Song Ki-baek,
and Song Ki-baek throws it!

863
00:50:07,838 --> 00:50:08,755
PN dodged it!

864
00:50:08,839 --> 00:50:10,841
Oh, Chan-yeong got hit. Chan-yeong is out.

865
00:50:10,924 --> 00:50:13,093
-Out!
-Nice one!

866
00:50:13,176 --> 00:50:15,011
-They weren't ready at all.
-That's right.

867
00:50:15,095 --> 00:50:17,514
-That's the first punch tactic.
-Land it to win.

868
00:50:17,597 --> 00:50:19,391
Ki-baek seems to be
in good spirits today.

869
00:50:19,474 --> 00:50:20,350
Yes.

870
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:26,273
I'M THE TEAM'S ACE!

871
00:50:26,356 --> 00:50:28,233
PN caught the ball. And shoot!

872
00:50:28,316 --> 00:50:30,944
-Ki-baek dodged. Dong-hyeok is out.
-Out!

873
00:50:31,027 --> 00:50:33,864
-Yes!
-Team Men on the Run has scored a point.

874
00:50:33,947 --> 00:50:35,782
It's not looking good for Team Donkeys.

875
00:50:35,866 --> 00:50:37,576
Oh? What?

876
00:50:37,659 --> 00:50:39,035
He looked at the camera.

877
00:50:39,119 --> 00:50:41,538
That finger heart.
That's why he's the team's ace.

878
00:50:41,621 --> 00:50:42,831
Let's go!

879
00:50:43,582 --> 00:50:44,416
KEEP THE MOMENTUM

880
00:50:44,499 --> 00:50:46,251
LET'S GO

881
00:50:53,425 --> 00:50:54,718
Song Ki-baek has the ball.

882
00:50:54,801 --> 00:50:57,095
Hold on.
What's with that look on his face?

883
00:50:57,179 --> 00:51:00,307
Hang on. He has crazy eyes right now.
Hold on.

884
00:51:04,770 --> 00:51:06,229
The ball left Crazy Eyes' hands.

885
00:51:06,313 --> 00:51:08,398
-Shoot!
-Shoot!

886
00:51:11,026 --> 00:51:12,027
Save!

887
00:51:13,069 --> 00:51:14,196
Wow, I survived.

888
00:51:14,279 --> 00:51:16,406
Kim Ung-min throws.
Is he after Song Ki-baek?

889
00:51:16,490 --> 00:51:19,409
Not a chance. Song Ki-baek looks around
and selects his target.

890
00:51:20,410 --> 00:51:23,246
Hold on. Song Ki-baek jumped.
He's floating in the air!

891
00:51:23,330 --> 00:51:27,417
Kang Ho-jun, Kang Seung-beom. Oh, PN!
That's the second headshot.

892
00:51:28,251 --> 00:51:29,753
Oh!

893
00:51:29,836 --> 00:51:31,296
-Save!
-It's a save.

894
00:51:31,379 --> 00:51:32,297
Damn it.

895
00:51:32,380 --> 00:51:34,674
PN looks very upset right now.

896
00:51:34,758 --> 00:51:36,134
Is he all right?

897
00:51:40,597 --> 00:51:41,598
Relax. Easy.

898
00:51:41,681 --> 00:51:42,849
Right. Sure thing.

899
00:51:42,933 --> 00:51:45,060
"Hey, relax." He lectured him.

900
00:51:45,143 --> 00:51:47,145
He only did that to throw him off.

901
00:51:47,229 --> 00:51:49,648
Oh! Song Ki-baek got the ball again.

902
00:51:53,985 --> 00:51:55,445
That's…

903
00:51:56,321 --> 00:51:58,907
-That is the deadly fire shot!
-Wait.

904
00:51:59,491 --> 00:52:01,243
PN is knocked out!

905
00:52:03,495 --> 00:52:05,413
Line crossed. Switch turns!

906
00:52:07,624 --> 00:52:10,502
-Hey, don't worry about it.
-Too bad. All right.

907
00:52:10,585 --> 00:52:11,461
Let's go get them.

908
00:52:11,545 --> 00:52:12,462
-All right.
-Okay.

909
00:52:12,546 --> 00:52:15,841
I told you to bring a variety show star,
not the Dodgeball King.

910
00:52:15,924 --> 00:52:18,802
He's done three headshots
just today alone.

911
00:52:19,386 --> 00:52:20,262
What's with him?

912
00:52:20,345 --> 00:52:22,430
No, I'm good. I don't need it.

913
00:52:22,514 --> 00:52:25,308
The cameras are rolling.
Why won't he drink the tea?

914
00:52:25,392 --> 00:52:27,018
Did you give him the sponsored products?

915
00:52:27,102 --> 00:52:29,479
-Well, I did.
-Okay.

916
00:52:29,563 --> 00:52:31,773
He thanked me and took extra products.

917
00:52:32,566 --> 00:52:35,485
Why? So he could have them at home?

918
00:52:35,569 --> 00:52:38,780
-What's his deal? Min-gu.
-Yes.

919
00:52:38,864 --> 00:52:40,031
Can we take a break?

920
00:52:40,115 --> 00:52:42,117
We'll take a short break.

921
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:43,869
I'll talk to him. Tidy up here.

922
00:52:44,953 --> 00:52:47,163
-We're doing pretty well.
-Did that hurt earlier?

923
00:52:47,247 --> 00:52:48,206
Ki-baek.

924
00:52:48,290 --> 00:52:49,249
Can we have a chat?

925
00:52:49,332 --> 00:52:50,750
-Sorry?
-Just a chat.

926
00:52:50,834 --> 00:52:52,752
Why? Oh, because I did so well.

927
00:52:52,836 --> 00:52:53,712
I'll be right back.

928
00:53:02,429 --> 00:53:03,263
Hello.

929
00:53:13,273 --> 00:53:15,901
HIGH VOLTAGE
KEEP OUT

930
00:53:15,984 --> 00:53:18,320
HIGH VOLTAGE
DO NOT TOUCH WITH BARE HANDS

931
00:53:25,327 --> 00:53:27,203
Ki-baek. Are you the Dodgeball King?

932
00:53:29,915 --> 00:53:31,875
Do you know the main theme of the show?

933
00:53:31,958 --> 00:53:35,879
A men's ball game, a showdown.
"Let's play together and have fun."

934
00:53:35,962 --> 00:53:37,047
Yes, exactly.

935
00:53:38,214 --> 00:53:41,051
Ball game, a showdown.
I think I'm doing a good job.

936
00:53:41,134 --> 00:53:43,762
No. What you said after that is
the most important part.

937
00:53:43,845 --> 00:53:46,806
"Let's play together and have fun."

938
00:53:46,890 --> 00:53:48,350
You're doing it all by yourself.

939
00:53:48,433 --> 00:53:52,062
Nothing's more important than chemistry
between cast members on a variety show.

940
00:53:53,146 --> 00:53:54,564
Oh, team play.

941
00:53:55,148 --> 00:53:56,983
I think I'm doing well on that front too.

942
00:53:57,067 --> 00:53:59,778
Forget it. Why do you keep targeting PN?

943
00:53:59,861 --> 00:54:00,695
His head, at that.

944
00:54:00,779 --> 00:54:03,323
We usually show PN's close-up
before the commercial break.

945
00:54:03,406 --> 00:54:05,533
At this rate, it'll begin
right after the headshot.

946
00:54:05,617 --> 00:54:08,036
That's because he's usually in the center.

947
00:54:08,119 --> 00:54:10,372
That's right. Why do you think that is?

948
00:54:10,455 --> 00:54:12,499
From the uniforms
to the lunch you guys had,

949
00:54:12,582 --> 00:54:15,460
PN's fans and the advertisers
prepared everything.

950
00:54:16,044 --> 00:54:16,878
Oh…

951
00:54:17,837 --> 00:54:20,465
I guess I didn't know
how things worked on the show.

952
00:54:22,509 --> 00:54:25,220
Oh, please. You know enough about showbiz.

953
00:54:25,303 --> 00:54:28,098
If you keep doing this,
people will call you an amateur.

954
00:54:31,559 --> 00:54:34,854
Even so, I am not an amateur.

955
00:54:55,291 --> 00:54:56,209
You excel at everything.

956
00:54:56,292 --> 00:54:58,461
You call this a news anchor?

957
00:54:58,545 --> 00:55:00,296
Can you cover my shift? Mr. Kim said…

958
00:55:19,733 --> 00:55:21,234
What is this? What's going on?

959
00:55:21,818 --> 00:55:22,902
What's going on?

960
00:55:22,986 --> 00:55:23,820
Is the power out?

961
00:55:23,903 --> 00:55:25,989
What? Why would the power go out?

962
00:55:31,411 --> 00:55:32,537
Mr. Song Ki-baek.

963
00:55:34,706 --> 00:55:37,083
Please wake up.

964
00:55:38,668 --> 00:55:39,794
Mr. Song!

965
00:55:40,920 --> 00:55:41,755
Yes?

966
00:55:42,839 --> 00:55:46,134
Ki-baek, are you all right?

967
00:55:47,594 --> 00:55:50,472
My God. Are you okay?

968
00:55:50,555 --> 00:55:51,556
Yes, I'm all right.

969
00:55:51,639 --> 00:55:52,807
Are you really okay?

970
00:55:52,891 --> 00:55:54,601
There were electric sparks everywhere.

971
00:55:54,684 --> 00:55:56,686
Who knew I'd see someone get
an electric shock?

972
00:55:56,770 --> 00:55:59,147
Are you really all right? You're okay?

973
00:55:59,230 --> 00:56:00,690
No, I'm not okay!

974
00:56:09,282 --> 00:56:10,450
What are you doing here?

975
00:56:10,533 --> 00:56:13,203
The power's out in the whole building.
Come out. Hurry!

976
00:56:16,081 --> 00:56:19,084
Shouldn't you go see a doctor?
I think you just had an electric shock.

977
00:56:19,167 --> 00:56:20,752
No, I feel fine physically,

978
00:56:20,835 --> 00:56:23,338
but I'm getting a headache
because you're so loud.

979
00:56:25,507 --> 00:56:26,508
I mean… Ma'am?

980
00:56:30,220 --> 00:56:31,638
You're not getting out?

981
00:56:31,721 --> 00:56:33,765
Ma'am? You're not getting out?

982
00:56:52,075 --> 00:56:54,160
Why did the power suddenly go out?

983
00:56:54,828 --> 00:56:56,955
Well, some stuff happened.

984
00:56:57,038 --> 00:56:59,040
-Did you call Facility Management?
-Yes.

985
00:56:59,124 --> 00:57:01,126
-I called them.
-It's so damn hot today.

986
00:57:01,793 --> 00:57:03,670
Do you want something to drink?

987
00:57:03,753 --> 00:57:04,921
Took you long enough.

988
00:57:06,339 --> 00:57:07,507
Are you messing with me?

989
00:57:07,590 --> 00:57:08,591
Don't you have something cold?

990
00:57:08,675 --> 00:57:10,218
And what are you waiting for?

991
00:57:10,301 --> 00:57:11,970
I feel so hot! Go get the umbrella.

992
00:57:12,053 --> 00:57:13,805
I'll get a sunburn on my face!

993
00:57:13,888 --> 00:57:15,098
Okay.

994
00:57:15,849 --> 00:57:16,850
Jesus Christ.

995
00:57:17,684 --> 00:57:19,477
PN is so cranky right now.

996
00:57:19,561 --> 00:57:21,855
What if he loses it
and throws a crazy tantrum?

997
00:57:21,938 --> 00:57:23,982
And here I thought
he was behaving himself.

998
00:57:25,233 --> 00:57:27,068
Oh, Ki-baek.

999
00:57:27,152 --> 00:57:27,986
Over here.

1000
00:57:30,238 --> 00:57:32,031
I knew you'd cause trouble.

1001
00:57:32,115 --> 00:57:34,409
What the heck did you do
to make the power go out?

1002
00:57:34,492 --> 00:57:36,619
It's always a nobody who causes trouble.

1003
00:57:36,703 --> 00:57:37,829
Loser.

1004
00:57:38,413 --> 00:57:39,789
Loser.

1005
00:57:42,625 --> 00:57:44,669
What? Why is that loser standing there?

1006
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:53,178
Are you trying to get my attention?

1007
00:57:53,261 --> 00:57:54,971
Then you really are--

1008
00:57:55,054 --> 00:57:56,181
No, I'm not.

1009
00:57:59,184 --> 00:58:00,935
Hey. You can't stand me, right?

1010
00:58:01,019 --> 00:58:02,187
Yes!

1011
00:58:03,980 --> 00:58:05,106
No.

1012
00:58:05,190 --> 00:58:06,524
I mean, no.

1013
00:58:06,608 --> 00:58:08,276
Oh, this guy is funny.

1014
00:58:08,860 --> 00:58:12,530
Oh, I see. You want to be my friend
because you want the spotlight.

1015
00:58:12,614 --> 00:58:14,532
I could help you if you'd like.

1016
00:58:14,616 --> 00:58:15,783
Then how about…

1017
00:58:17,827 --> 00:58:20,413
you do as I say? All right?

1018
00:58:22,040 --> 00:58:23,333
That's how it works here.

1019
00:58:23,917 --> 00:58:26,294
There are many eyes watching,
so don't fight here.

1020
00:58:26,377 --> 00:58:28,129
-I-na, take Ki-baek.
-Just avoid him.

1021
00:58:28,213 --> 00:58:30,340
Come here, PN. Let's talk.

1022
00:58:30,423 --> 00:58:31,257
Talk about what?

1023
00:58:31,341 --> 00:58:33,051
Let's just go.

1024
00:58:33,134 --> 00:58:34,511
No, I don't want to.

1025
00:58:34,594 --> 00:58:37,514
I'll chew that jerk to pieces today…

1026
00:58:41,142 --> 00:58:42,227
Please calm down.

1027
00:58:42,310 --> 00:58:43,561
He keeps provoking me.

1028
00:58:43,645 --> 00:58:46,105
-Calm down--
-Damn you! What are you doing?

1029
00:58:46,189 --> 00:58:48,358
I did nothing wrong, okay?

1030
00:58:48,441 --> 00:58:49,734
Min-gu!

1031
00:58:50,568 --> 00:58:51,736
No, it's not that.

1032
00:58:54,781 --> 00:58:56,950
I'm sorry, PN. My apologies.

1033
00:58:57,033 --> 00:59:00,370
Loser. He's apologizing again.

1034
00:59:01,120 --> 00:59:03,248
Park Jin-bok!

1035
00:59:09,963 --> 00:59:10,964
Park Jin-bok?

1036
00:59:11,047 --> 00:59:13,091
He hates it when someone
says his real name.

1037
00:59:13,174 --> 00:59:14,551
We're screwed.

1038
00:59:21,140 --> 00:59:22,392
Why did you apologize?

1039
00:59:23,601 --> 00:59:24,727
Have you lost your mind?

1040
00:59:25,311 --> 00:59:28,439
I thought you were a clown,
but are you just plain crazy?

1041
00:59:29,023 --> 00:59:30,692
Hey! Forget about the shoot.

1042
00:59:32,777 --> 00:59:35,405
Get this psycho out of my sight!

1043
00:59:36,823 --> 00:59:38,491
Get your act together!

1044
00:59:38,575 --> 00:59:40,868
Everyone you see right now
is here to work.

1045
00:59:40,952 --> 00:59:45,081
No one came here to be harassed
by a crazy bastard like you!

1046
00:59:45,164 --> 00:59:48,209
Do you think everyone's a joke
because they let you have your way?

1047
00:59:48,793 --> 00:59:50,336
-Let go, okay?
-Park Jin-bok!

1048
00:59:51,004 --> 00:59:52,171
What should we do?

1049
00:59:52,255 --> 00:59:54,090
Jin-bok can't fight. Just leave them be.

1050
00:59:54,173 --> 00:59:55,133
You!

1051
00:59:56,509 --> 00:59:58,011
You're successful because of your fans.

1052
00:59:58,094 --> 01:00:02,473
If you remain such an ingrate,
someone will screw you over.

1053
01:00:02,557 --> 01:00:05,226
You deserve to get screwed over, big-time!

1054
01:00:07,061 --> 01:00:09,397
Just one slap in the face from me,

1055
01:00:09,480 --> 01:00:11,399
and you'll turn over a new leaf.

1056
01:00:11,983 --> 01:00:13,651
You rude bastard!

1057
01:00:13,735 --> 01:00:14,986
Mr. Song Ki-baek!

1058
01:00:18,823 --> 01:00:20,742
-What?
-Oh, no. Woo-ju!

1059
01:00:26,623 --> 01:00:28,458
-What is this?
-Have you lost your mind?

1060
01:00:28,541 --> 01:00:31,794
What… What's happening?

1061
01:00:31,878 --> 01:00:33,171
What?

1062
01:00:33,254 --> 01:00:35,089
No, no way. Trust me.

1063
01:00:35,173 --> 01:00:37,759
This can't be.

1064
01:00:37,842 --> 01:00:38,968
No, no. No way!

1065
01:00:39,052 --> 01:00:40,678
This has got to be a lie.

1066
01:00:41,304 --> 01:00:44,390
This is all a lie!

1067
01:01:11,709 --> 01:01:13,544
FRANKLY SPEAKING

1068
01:01:14,253 --> 01:01:16,297
You've changed. You're acting strange.

1069
01:01:16,881 --> 01:01:18,925
So I can't say what I don't mean.

1070
01:01:19,008 --> 01:01:20,009
Does this even make sense?

1071
01:01:21,928 --> 01:01:24,055
I respect you? No, I don't.

1072
01:01:24,138 --> 01:01:26,349
This is so damn stressful.

1073
01:01:26,432 --> 01:01:28,226
-Get out, moron!
-Apologize!

1074
01:01:30,228 --> 01:01:33,690
Song Ki-baek. I'm worried.

1075
01:01:36,109 --> 01:01:37,694
Are you all right?

1076
01:01:37,777 --> 01:01:38,653
It's dangerous!

1077
01:01:38,736 --> 01:01:40,405
-Get out of my sight!
-Stop!

1078
01:01:41,489 --> 01:01:42,865
I'm sorry!

1079
01:01:43,700 --> 01:01:48,705
